    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Build The System","date":"2016-02-15","tags":["typography","poster","software"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/2032ecc015f3cb17668dbbb176fe49c9/poster.png"}},"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/817fb/with-bg.webp 200w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/8429e/with-bg.webp 400w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/e8af0/with-bg.webp 800w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/e9f1f/with-bg.webp 1200w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/76e7d/with-bg.png 200w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/ca202/with-bg.png 400w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/36e56/with-bg.png 800w,\n/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/7b58d/with-bg.png 1200w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/5c3096aefed5c236e895dedb5033e4f1/36e56/with-bg.png\"\n            alt=\"Build the System poster\"\n            title=\"Build the System poster\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Designers often work with a system, whether it is a grid on a page or a typographical hierarchy. This poster is an exploration into building and revealing a system by gradually breaking away from it. In my own design practice, I start my process by building a system, usually by means of computer programming. Typography in this poster is first created with Processing programming language with a few simple rules. Changing a few parameters of the rules allows me to explore many forms it can create. But eventually, there comes a time when the rigid rules cannot apply any more, and that is when the instinct and manual interventions are needed.</p>\n<h3>Publications and Awards</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The T Magazine, Korea, 2017</li>\n<li>Gold Winner, Graphis Poster Annual, 2016</li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Designers often work with a system, whether it is a grid on a page or a typographical hierarchy. This poster is an exploration into building…"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/work/2016-build-the-system/"}},
